e organized under the Usage section: prerequisites, customization methods for forbidden tags and attributes, configuration options for HTML checking, how to modify check contents, and test execution verification procedures. The current knowledge file organization needs adjustment—the HTML4.01 differences section should be separated from the main specifications, and these subsections should be properly nested under Usage rather than appearing as top-level sections. I'm checking the RST heading hierarchy in the source document. The top-level title uses equals signs, then 目的 and 仕様 are h2 sections marked with equals signs, while HTML4.01との相違点 and the subsections under 使用方法 are h3 sections marked with dashes. So there are three h2 sections total (目的, 仕様, 使用方法) and six h3 sections, which means the knowledge file's merging of 目的 and 仕様 into the first section is acceptable since smaller sections can be consolidated.\n\nNow I'm verifying that all the required code hints are present for each section. For the HTMLチェック内容の変更 section, I see HtmlChecker, InvalidHtmlException, HttpTestConfiguration, SimpleHtmlChecker, and htmlChecker are all accounted for. The 使用禁止タグ・属性のカスタマイズ方法 section has htmlCheckerConfig, HttpTestConfiguration, and the CSV config file. The HTMLチェック実行要否の設定方法 section has checkHtml and HttpTestConfiguration. Everything checks out so far.\n\nNow I'm comparing what s1 says about the default configuration against the source material. The source provides more detail—it explains that the default settings include deprecated tags and attributes from W3C, introduces the abbreviated term \"非推奨タグ・属性,\" and notes that customization allows changing which tags and attributes are prohibited. The statement in s1 captures the essence but is more concise, referencing the W3C official site and pointing to the customization section. s3の設定ファイルについて、ソースには「デフォルト設定を使用する場合、プロジェクト開始時に設定変更は不要」という重要な情報が含まれているのに、ナレッジファイルではこれが省略されている。ユーザーがカスタマイズの必要性を判断する際に必要な情報なので、これは見落としだ。次のセクションではテストプロジェクトの